<!-- END APPRAISAL FORM -->
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I know how Mount Cotton buyers think. Lifestyle buyers and acreage purchasers do not shop the way standard residential buyers do. They are travelling from inner Brisbane, the Gold Coast and interstate, often inspect only on weekends, and have a clear mental list of what working acreage should include: useable land, water security, sheds and a quality main dwelling. Pricing a Mount Cotton property requires understanding that bank valuations and online tools regularly understate what well-presented acreage achieves at sale.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Sirromet Wines and the surrounding bushland reserves give Mount Cotton its destination feel, and the suburb's road links via Mount Cotton Road through to Capalaba mean lifestyle buyers can still commute to the inner south or CBD. The best results consistently come from properties with cleared, useable acreage, dwellings that are in genuine move-in condition, and infrastructure such as town-water access where available, large sheds, dam or tank capacity and stockyards or fenced paddocks. Buyers price these features in carefully, and a campaign that highlights them properly will outperform a generic acreage listing.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #c4912a;">
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:400; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:0.4rem;">Mount Cotton Specialist</p>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:300; color:#6b6560;">Redlands acreage market</p>
      </div>
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #c4912a;">
